  "strategy": [
    "Alternate between short forward moves and full scans in exploration to maximize marker detection chances.",
    "On marker_seen, immediately switch to marker tracking and approach behaviors, prioritizing move_to_marker.",
    "If marker is lost during tracking, initiate a scan to reacquire.",
    "On marker_close, transition to a terminal stop state to safely complete the task.",
    "Obstacle recovery uses move_backward followed by a scan; obs_left prefers rotate_clockwise, obs_right prefers rotate_counterclockwise to avoid oscillations.",
    "All uncontrollable events are handled deterministically in every state.",
    "Helper commit states ensure one-shot actions and prevent infinite loops.",
    "No direct move_forward from obs_front; always require a recovery step.",
    "Exploration never stalls: at least one controllable is always enabled in non-terminal states."
  ]
